<item>
            <title>[HBASE-15294] Document advanced replication configurations with security</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15294</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14866&quot; title=&quot;VerifyReplication should use peer configuration in peer connection&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-14866&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-14866&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixed handling of source and cluster replication configs for some replication tools, needed, for example, for correct handling of some cross-realm trust security configurations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to document some examples in the reference guide.  One examle, to configure a replication peer with different server principals:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;add_peer &apos;1&apos;, CLUSTER_KEY =&amp;gt; &quot;server1.cie.com:2181:/hbase&quot;,
    CONFIG =&amp;gt; {
        &apos;hbase.master.kerberos.principal&apos; =&amp;gt; &apos;hbase/instance2@REALM2.COM&apos;,
        &apos;hbase.regionserver.kerberos.principal&apos; =&amp;gt; &apos;hbase/instance2@REALM2.COM&apos;,
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Additional arguments to VerifyReplication should also be documented in the usage output.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
